Srinagar, June 26: Ahead of Muharram, the Srinagar police have issued a public advisory urging people to observe the procession with peace, dignity and discipline.
In a handout to GNS, the police said that maintain peace, discipline and communal harmony throughout the procession.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Follow all directions issued by the administration and police authorities.Cooperate with traffic police and volunteers for smooth movement.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ensure the procession remains confined to the permitted route and purpose. Respect the religious sentiments and beliefs of all communities.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Protect public and government property and maintain cleanliness. Do not indulge in any unlawful activity or create any law &amp; order situation.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Do not raise provocative slogans, make inflammatory speeches or engage in activities that may outrage religious sentiments. Do not obstruct traffic flow or movement of pedestrians.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Do not damage, deface or misuse government/public property. Do not display provocative banners, posters, placards, flags etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;
Do not disrespect the National Flag or glorify any country, organization or group. Do not carry or display flags/symbols of any country, organization or group. Do not engage in any activity detrimental to the integrity, sovereignty and unity of the Nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;
The advisory said public cooperation will ensure a peaceful and dignified observance of Muharram, based on the principles of peace, respect, harmony and responsibility, reads the statement.(GNS)
